paragraph.content:
information on every person who undergoes a reproductive technology
                        procedure in those premises at any time on or after the commencement of
                            Part 3;

a reproductive technology procedure shall not be provided to a person unless
                account has been taken of the welfare of any child who may be born in consequence of
                the procedure;

subparagraph.content:
each case of sex selection achieved through a reproductive technology
                    procedure shall be reported to the Council within 3 months after the procedure
                    has taken place;

paragraph.content:
prior approval of the Council shall be obtained for carrying on any
                reproductive technology procedure involving tissue typing in conjunction with
                preimplantation genetic diagnosis in the licensed premises;

subparagraph.content:
if other gametes or embryos of the donor are stored in the licensed
                    premises under another licence, a person to whom that licence applies;
                    and

paragraph.continued:
shall be established for the purpose of ensuring that no more than 3 live
                birth events are brought about by the gametes or embryos donated by any single
                donor;

paragraph.content:
a system shall be established and maintained so as to ensure that proper
                practices and procedures are adopted and followed in the licensed
                premises;

a person shall not be allowed to collect his or her own gametes or embryos
                    from the licensed premises except in circumstances specified in the
                    code;

subparagraph.content:
the period up to the time when the donated gametes or embryos have
                        brought about 3 live birth events, or such other number of live birth events
                        as specified by the donor, whichever is smaller;

paragraph.content:
in the case of a person whose gametes or embryos are stored for use in a
                    reproductive technology procedure to be provided to the person, 10
                    years;

except as otherwise provided by the code, in the case of a donation made by
                    the donor to a recipient designated by the donor in the circumstances permitted
                    under the code, 2 years;

subsection.def:
complaint
                    (申訴) means a complaint lodged under
                    section 17(1);
